history.content:
The ASUC Office of Senator Elif Sensurucu and Berkeley Entrepreneurs Association, along with Entrepreneurs@Berkeley, are organizing the ASUC & BEA Startup Expo II. We would like to invite you to attend the event! It's taking place on Monday, April 25th from 5pm – 7pm, at Chou Hall 6th floor, Spieker Forum. UC Berkeley, Stanford, and Carnegie Mellon undergraduate, PhD and MBA students will be partaking in this event. Please feel free to share this opportunity with all of your members, friends and students. 

 

Here is the Startup Application link (deadline April 18th):

tinyurl.com/asucstartupexpo

 

Here is the Attendee Sign-up link (only 180 spots):

tinyurl.com/asucstartupattn

 

Attire for this event is business casual.

 

If you have any questions or comments, you can contact me at ryusei.best@berkeley.edu

 

Hope to see all of you there!

 

Ryusei Best Hayashi

ASUC Director of International Affairs in Office of Senator Sensurucu

 

Ryusei Best Hayashi

Director of International Affairs in the ASUC Office of Senator Sensurucu

Associated Students of the University of California
